  <Slide id="personalization" variant="dark">
    <div class="content-slide personalization">
      <p class="overline">The Real Lesson</p>
      <h2><span class="highlight">Own</span> Your Harness</h2>
      <p class="lead personalization__lead">The harness is the layer between you and the model. Most people accept whatever ships. The leverage is in controlling it yourself.</p>

      <div class="contrast">
        <div class="contrast__col contrast__col--default">
          <p class="contrast__kicker">The untouched default</p>
          <ul class="contrast__list">
            <li>Context injected behind your back</li>
            <li>Prompts &amp; tools change every release</li>
            <li>Bloat you can&rsquo;t see or remove</li>
            <li>Subagents: a black box in a black box</li>
            <li>Your workflow breaks when they ship</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="contrast__vs" aria-hidden="true">vs</div>

        <div class="contrast__col contrast__col--you">
          <p class="contrast__kicker">A harness you own</p>
          <ul class="contrast__list">
            <li>Inspect every model interaction</li>
            <li>Stable &mdash; you decide when it changes</li>
            <li>Shaped to your work, not the median</li>
            <li>Extend it yourself &mdash; or have it extend itself</li>
            <li>You understand what it&rsquo;s doing, and why</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="contrast__bridge">
        <p class="contrast__bridge-line">&ldquo;Change the harness, <em>not your workflow.</em>&rdquo;</p>
        <p class="contrast__bridge-sub">The philosophy behind <strong>Pi</strong> &mdash; and there&rsquo;s more than one way to get there.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Slide>

  <!-- Slide 10: Personalization how-to (the five dials) -->
  <Slide id="personalization-how" variant="accent">
    <div class="content-slide personalization-how">
      <p class="overline">Make It Yours</p>
      <h2>Two Ways to <span class="highlight">Own It</span></h2>
      <p class="lead personalization-how__lead">Both are real ownership. They differ in where you start &mdash; not in whether you&rsquo;re in control.</p>

      <div class="roads">
        <div class="road road--adopt">
          <div class="road__head">
            <span class="road__badge">Start rich</span>
            <h3 class="road__title">Adopt &amp; Make It Yours</h3>
            <span class="road__example">e.g. Oh-My-OpenAgent on OpenCode</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="road__list">
            <li>Begin from a rich, opinionated harness</li>
            <li>Inherit batteries &mdash; routing, continuation, guardrails</li>
            <li>Tune the dials to your role and taste</li>
            <li>Disable, override, and rewrite what doesn&rsquo;t fit</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="road__trade"><span class="road__trade-label">Trade</span> Powerful on day one &mdash; you learn the internals as you reshape them.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="road road--build">
          <div class="road__head">
            <span class="road__badge">Start minimal</span>
            <h3 class="road__title">Build It Up Yourself</h3>
            <span class="road__example">e.g. Pi &mdash; a minimal harness</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="road__list">
            <li>Begin from primitives: 4 tools, a tiny prompt, a model API</li>
            <li>Add only what you actually reach for</li>
            <li>Self-modifying &mdash; &ldquo;just ask it to build it&rdquo;</li>
            <li>See and control every model call from the start</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="road__trade"><span class="road__trade-label">Trade</span> Total transparency &mdash; you assemble the power yourself.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="roads__destination">
        <p class="roads__destination-line">Either way you end up somewhere you chose: a harness that <em>fits you, that you understand, that doesn&rsquo;t change under you.</em></p>
        <p class="roads__destination-sub">The only losing move is leaving the default untouched.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Slide>

